<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-07-07T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-07-07T18:00:00-05:00" n="353" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">124.842/127: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-07T19:00:00-04:00">July 7, 1936—7
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>298. Your 453, July 6, 7 p.m., and 454, July 6, 10 p.m. Department
                                approves of your action with understanding that other legations
                                possessing radio stations receive no more favorable treatment than
                                that accorded to American Legation.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>